texts.text: That's it.
>You and the others reach the Elements' headquarters.
>Lookouts are visible around the building.
With the Neo Liberators gone, we are their only remaining foe.
The Elements' attention is turned to our headquarters,

making their rear guard weak...
Or so I thought.
But we don't have the time for a head-on offensive.
Our headquarters are under attack even now.
I'll be a decoy.
Let me be a decoy.
A viable solution indeed. You've really wised up.
Very well. Take this then.
It's a flash-bang. Stuns enemies with light and sound.
Throw it when you're in retreat.

Oh, and...don't kill anyone.
That'd be a problem later.
I'll slip inside and search for Tupsimati.
Once destroyed, I'll fire three shots. That means evacuate.
Now get going. Let me see what you can do.

The enemy...
Just as Period foresaw.
Just one, though. That ex-Liberator turncoat.
The Brotherhood's really running short on personnel, huh?
Prepare yourself! This is the end for you.
>Explosions and fighting can be heard in the distance.
So, it's begun. Let's hope I can finish up quickly...
A barrier? Guess Period saw this strategy coming.
Could my allied demons break it?
Damn, there's no time for this—
Baal!
Yah!
>The barrier covering the building is destroyed.
What was that noise!
They broke through! This was just a distraction!
I'm going back in! You take care of this—
>The Elements turn away.
>And your demon blocks their path.
Shit, we gotta deal with this first! All hands on deck!
Can you get through?
You... You're the one they call the "Alternate Hero."

Aw shucks, you remember me?
I'm totally honored.
Why help me? You're a Neo Liberator, no?
Well, I'm not exactly helping you, per se...
It's more that I'm helping Newbie. [sys user_name], that is.
But who cares, really? I won't get in your way.
Not like you have time for chit-chat, right?
Do as you like.
Sure thing. So, what are you up to, anyway?
Setting this up.
...Gotcha.
Destroying the barrier alerted them I'm here.
But they're in total chaos.
They likely didn't expect anyone to destroy it.
Seems dumb.

It was a rather strong barrier.
Didn't stop you, though.

Aw, is that a compliment?
Be still, my heart!
I could do with less of that, thanks.
You say you want to help [sys user_name]. Doesn't add up.
Why take such an indirect route through me?
Seeing a Neo Liberator alive might have been enough
for them to leave the Brotherhood and join you.
Strong as you are, you could have made contact by now.

Well, you see...
It's just a wee bit complicated.
I'm not exactly a regular, if you know what I mean.
Now that the Neo Liberators are mostly destroyed,
cooperation is more of an anomaly than anything else...
I didn't wanna get in the way of his decision, I guess?
You dropped the sass but you're still being unclear.

I wasn't expecting any of this.
That's all I can say.
...Hmph.
So, this is Tupsimati.
Over there! Intruder!

Persistent little...
Don't you dare get in my way!
Baal!
Can you get through?

Aw shucks, you remember me?
I'm totally honored.
Well, I'm not exactly helping you, per se...
It's more that I'm helping Newbie. [sys user_name], that is.

So, let's leave it at that.
No skin off your back.
Not like you have time for chit-chat, right?
Sure thing. So, what are you up to, anyway?
...Gotcha.
But they're in total chaos.
Seems dumb.

Aw, is that a compliment?
Be still, my heart!

Well, you see...
It's just a wee bit complicated.
I'm not exactly a regular, if you know what I mean.
Now that the Neo Liberators are mostly destroyed,
cooperation is more of an anomaly than anything else...
I didn't wanna get in the way of her decision, I guess?

I wasn't expecting any of this.
That's all I can say.
